cells.name: Empty
cells.description: Nothing.

cells.name: Wall
cells.description: Unbreakable. This also implies being immovable.

cells.name: Mover
cells.description: Constantly attempts to move forwards, pushing stuff in it's way.

cells.name: Generator
cells.description: Clones the cell behind it and pushes it out the front.

cells.name: Pushable
cells.description: Does nothing; Can be moved in any direction.

cells.name: Slider
cells.description: Can only be moved towards the marked directions.

cells.name: One-Directional
cells.description: Can only be moved towards the marked directions.

cells.name: Two-Directional
cells.description: Can only be moved towards the marked directions.

cells.name: Three-Directional
cells.description: Can only be moved towards the marked directions.

cells.name: CW Rotator
cells.description: Rotates neighboring cells 90 degrees clockwise.

cells.name: CCW Rotator
cells.description: Rotates neighboring cells 90 degrees counter-clockwise.

cells.name: 180 Rotator
cells.description: Rotates neighboring cells 180 degrees.

cells.name: Trash
cells.description: Deletes all cells that go into it. Is unbreakable, but can be rotated.

cells.name: Enemy
cells.description:
When a cell touches it, it kills both itself and the cell that it collided with.
Enemy-tagged by default, meaning it must be destroyed to complete a level.

cells.name: Puller
cells.description: Moves forward and pulls cells. Can not push.

cells.name: Mirror
cells.description: Swaps the two cells it's arrows point to. Swap force ignores divergers.

cells.name: Diverger
cells.description: Diverts whatever comes into it through the arrow.

cells.name: Redirector
cells.description: Sets the rotation of neighboring cells to it's own rotation. Cannot be affected by other Redirectors.

cells.name: CW Gear
cells.description: Rotates surrounding cells around itself clockwise using swap force. Gets jammed by unbreakable cells and other Gears.

cells.name: CCW Gear
cells.description: Rotates surrounding cells around itself counter-clockwise using swap force. Gets jammed by unbreakable cells and other Gears.

cells.name: Ungeneratable
cells.description: When something tries to generate it, it will instead generate nothing but force.

cells.name: Repulsor
cells.description: Applies a pushing force in 4 directions.

cells.name: Weight
cells.description: Absorbs 1 unit of force.

cells.name: Cross Generator
cells.description: Two generators combined.

cells.name: Strong Enemy
cells.description: An enemy that takes two hits to kill.

cells.name: Freezer
cells.description: Stops the cells adjacent to it from activating.

cells.name: CW Generator
cells.description: Clockwise-bent Generator.

cells.name: CCW Generator
cells.description: Counter-clockwise-bent Generator.

cells.name: Advancer
cells.description: Puller + Mover.

cells.name: Impulsor
cells.description: Pulls cells towards it in 4 directions.

cells.name: Flipper
cells.description: Flips cells based on it's rotation; if it's horizontal, it flips horizontally, and vertically if it's orientated vertically.

cells.name: Bidiverger
cells.description: Two Divergers combined.

cells.name: OR Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A or B) is true. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: AND Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A and B) is true. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: XOR Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A != B) is true. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: NOR Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A or B) is false. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: NAND Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A and B) is false. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: XNOR Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A != B) is false. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: Straight Diverger
cells.description: Diverger with no bend.

cells.name: Cross Diverger
cells.description: Two Straight divergers combined.

cells.name: Twist Generator
cells.description: Flips the cell that it generates, across the same axis as the arrow.

cells.name: Ghost
cells.description: Wall that can not be generated.

cells.name: Bias
cells.description: Adds to any force going it's direction and subtracts from any force going against it.

cells.name: Shield
cells.description: Prevents the cells surrounding it from colliding with enemies or being affected by dangerous forces like infection or transformation.

cells.name: Intaker
cells.description: Pulls cells that are in front of it towards it. The front acts like a trash cell.

cells.name: Replicator
cells.description: Clones the cell in front of it.

cells.name: Cross Replicator
cells.description: Two Replicators combined.

cells.name: Fungal
cells.description: When this cell is pushed, the cell that pushed it will be converted into another Fungal cell.

cells.name: Forker
cells.description: Like a Diverger that clones the cell.

cells.name: Triforker
cells.description: Forker with three outputs.

cells.name: Super Repulsor
cells.description: Pushes cells across infinite distance with infinite force.

cells.name: Demolisher
cells.description: Similar to a trash cell, but when a cell is pushed in, the demolisher destroys it's neighbors.

cells.name: Opposition
cells.description: Can only be pushed, pulled, or grabbed towards certain directions, indicated by the arrows.

cells.name: Cross Opposition
cells.description: Two Oppositions combined.

cells.name: Slider Opposition
cells.description: Opposition that only restricts two sides, while the others are pushable.

cells.name: Super Generator
cells.description: A Generator that generates the entire row of cells behind it.

cells.name: Cross Mirror
cells.description: Two mirrors combined.

cells.name: Birotator
cells.description: Rotates CW on one half and CCW on the other half.

cells.name: Driller
cells.description: Attempts to swaps the cell in front of it with itself.

cells.name: Auger
cells.description:
Driller + Mover.
Attempts to push before drilling.

cells.name: Corkscrew
cells.description: Driller + Puller + Mover.

cells.name: Bringer
cells.description: Driller + Puller.

cells.name: Outwards Redirector
cells.description: Forces neighboring cells to face away from itself.

cells.name: Inwards Redirector
cells.description: Forces neighboring cells to face towards itself.

cells.name: CW Redirector
cells.description: Forces neighboring cells to face clockwise around itself.

cells.name: CCW Redirector
cells.description: Forces neighboring cells to face counter-clockwise around itself.

cells.name: CW Semirotator
cells.description: Only rotates on 2 faces.

cells.name: CCW Semirotator
cells.description: Only rotates on 2 faces.

cells.name: 180 Semirotator
cells.description: Only rotates on 2 faces.

cells.name: Tough Slider
cells.description: Acts like a wall on 2 sides and like a push on the other 2.

cells.name: Pararotator
cells.description: Rotates CW on two sides and CCW on the other two sides.

cells.name: Grabber
cells.description: Drags the cells to it's sides along with it.

cells.name: Heaver
cells.description: Grabber + Mover.

cells.name: Lugger
cells.description: Puller + Grabber.

cells.name: Hoister
cells.description: Puller + Grabber + Mover.

cells.name: Raker
cells.description: Driller + Grabber.

cells.name: Borer
cells.description: Grabber + Mover + Driller.

cells.name: Carrier
cells.description: Puller + Grabber + Driller.

cells.name: Omnipower
cells.description: Puller + Grabber + Mover + Driller.

cells.name: Ice
cells.description: Causes cells to slip past when they move near it.

cells.name: Tetramirror
cells.description: 4 mirrors combined.

cells.name: CW Grapulsor
cells.description: Applies clockwise grabbing force to it's neighbors.

cells.name: CCW Grapulsor
cells.description: Applies counter-clockwise grabbing force to it's neighbors.

cells.name: Bivalve Diverger
cells.description: Valve Diverger with three inputs.

cells.name: CW Paravalve Diverger
cells.description: Straight Diverger with two extra curved inputs.

cells.name: CCW Paravalve Diverger
cells.description: Straight Diverger with two extra curved inputs.

cells.name: Bivalve Displacer
cells.description: Bivalve Diverger that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CW Paravalve Displacer
cells.description: CW Paravalve Diverger that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CCW Paravalve Displacer
cells.description: CCW Paravalve Diverger that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: Semiflipper A
cells.description: Only flips on 2 sides.

cells.name: Semiflipper B
cells.description: Only flips on 2 sides.

cells.name: Displacer
cells.description: Diverger that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: Bidisplacer
cells.description: Bidiverger that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CW Valve Diverger
cells.description: One-way Diverger with two input faces.

cells.name: CCW Valve Diverger
cells.description: One-way Diverger with two input faces.

cells.name: CW Valve Displacer
cells.description: CW Valve Diverger that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CCW Valve Displacer
cells.description: CCW Valve Diverger that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CW Forker
cells.description: Forker with a straight and rotated output.

cells.name: CCW Forker
cells.description: Forker with a straight and rotated output.

cells.name: Divider
cells.description: Forker that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: Tridivider
cells.description: Triforker that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CW Divider
cells.description: CW Forker that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CCW Divider
cells.description: CCW Forker that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: Conditional
cells.description:
The weight of this cell depends on it's rotation.
(0-3, increases clockwise)

cells.name: Anti-Weight
cells.description: Adds 1 unit of force to applied forces.

cells.name: Transmitter
cells.description: When rotated, flipped, or given an effect such as protection, it applies the effects to it's neighbors aswell.

cells.name: Shifter
cells.description: Pulls cells in from the back and pushes them out the front.

cells.name: Cross Shifter
cells.description: Two Shifters combined.

cells.name: CW Minigear
cells.description: CW Gear that only affects 4 cells.

cells.name: CCW Minigear
cells.description: CCW Gear that only affects 4 cells.

cells.name: CW Cloner
cells.description: CW Generator that does not rotate the generated cell.

cells.name: CCW Cloner
cells.description: CCW Generator that does not rotate the generated cell.

cells.name: Locker
cells.description: Prevents the cells adjacent to it from being rotated or flipped.

cells.name: Redirect Generator
cells.description: Generator that rotates the generated cell so it faces the same way as itself.

cells.name: Nudger
cells.description: Moves forward, but does not push cells.

cells.name: Slicer
cells.description: Moves forward; upon hitting a cell, it will attempt to push the cell out of the way in a direction perpendicular to it's own.

cells.name: Full Marker
cells.description: Decoration. Transparent to cells; disappears after being moved onto.

cells.name: X Marker
cells.description: Decoration. Transparent to cells; disappears after being moved onto.

cells.name: Warning Marker
cells.description: Decoration. Transparent to cells; disappears after being moved onto.

cells.name: Check Marker
cells.description: Decoration. Transparent to cells; disappears after being moved onto.

cells.name: Question Marker
cells.description: Decoration. Transparent to cells; disappears after being moved onto.

cells.name: Arrow Marker
cells.description: Decoration. Transparent to cells; disappears after being moved onto.

cells.name: Diagonal Arrow Marker
cells.description: Decoration. Transparent to cells; disappears after being moved onto.

cells.name: Crimson
cells.description: Turns adjacent cells into Crimson cells.

cells.name: Warped
cells.description: Turns diagonally adjacent cells into Warped cells.

cells.name: Corruption
cells.description: Turns surrounding cells into Corruption cells.

cells.name: Hallow
cells.description: Unbreakable. When a cell tries to push it, it turns into a another Hallow.

cells.name: Cancer
cells.description: Similar to Crimson, but can spread onto air cells.

cells.name: Bacteria
cells.description: Similar to Crimson, but can ONLY spread onto air cells.

cells.name: Bioweapon
cells.description: Similar to Warped, but can spread onto air cells.

cells.name: Prion
cells.description: Similar to Warped, but can ONLY spread onto air cells.

cells.name: Grey Goo
cells.description: Similar to Corruption, but can spread onto air cells.

cells.name: Virus
cells.description: Similar to Corruption, but can ONLY spread onto air cells.

cells.name: Tumor
cells.description: Similar to Bacteria, but only spreads 50% of the time.

cells.name: Infection
cells.description: Similar to Crimson, but only spreads 50% of the time.

cells.name: Pathogen
cells.description: Similar to Cancer, but only spreads 50% of the time.

cells.name: Push Clamper
cells.description: Prevents cells from being pushed.

cells.name: Pull Clamper
cells.description: Prevents cells from being pulled.

cells.name: Grab Clamper
cells.description: Prevents cells from being grabbed.

cells.name: Swap Clamper
cells.description: Prevents cells from being swapped.

cells.name: Tough Two-Directional
cells.description: Acts like a wall on 2 sides (+1 corner) and like a push on the other 2.

cells.name: Megademolisher
cells.description: Similar to a Demolisher, but affects diagonal neighbors too.

cells.name: Resistance
cells.description: Can only be pushed with exactly 1 unit of force.

cells.name: Tentative
cells.description:
Like Resistance, but the amount of force it needs is dependant on it's rotation.
(1-4, increases clockwise)

cells.name: Restrictor
cells.description: Only allows 1 unit of force to pass through.

cells.name: Megashield
cells.description: Like a Shield, but affects a 5x5 area.

cells.name: Timewarper
cells.description: Reverts the space it's pointing at back to what it was in the initial state.

cells.name: Time Generator
cells.description: Generates whatever the space behind it had in the initial state.

cells.name: Cross Timewarper
cells.description: Two Timewarpers in one.

cells.name: Life
cells.description:
Spreads like Conway's Game of Life.
Infects non-Life cells.

cells.name: CW Spinner
cells.description: Unbreakable. When a cell touches it, it rotates the cell clockwise.

cells.name: CCW Spinner
cells.description: Unbreakable. When a cell touches it, it rotates the cell counter-clockwise.

cells.name: 180 Spinner
cells.description: Unbreakable. When a cell touches it, it rotates the cell 180 degrees.

cells.name: Key
cells.description: When it gets pushed into a Door cell, it destroys itself and the Door.

cells.name: Door
cells.description: Unbreakable, but when a Key cell is pushed into it they destroy eachother.

cells.name: Cross Intaker
cells.description: Two Intakers combined.

cells.name: Magnet
cells.description: Magnets can attract or repel each other. Same colors repel, different colors attract.

cells.name: Tough One-Directional
cells.description: Acts like a wall on 3 sides and like a push on one.

cells.name: Tough Three-Directional
cells.description: Acts like a wall on 1 side (+2 corners) and like a push on the other 3.

cells.name: Tough Pushable
cells.description: Can't be affected by cells diagonally.

cells.name: Missile
cells.description: Like a moving enemy, but it isn't enemy-tagged.

cells.name: Life Missile
cells.description: Upon hitting something, it turns into a Life cell.

cells.name: Staller
cells.description: Like a Wall, but upon collision, it will be destroyed.

cells.name: Bulk Enemy
cells.description:
Like an Enemy, but it will also stop force similar to a Wall.
In other words, a Staller that also destroys the attacking cell.

cells.name: Swivel Enemy
cells.description:
The HP of this enemy is measured by it's rotation.
(1-4, increases clockwise)

cells.name: Storage
cells.description: If a cell moves into it, it will store the cell until another cell bumps it out.

cells.name: Memory Generator
cells.description: Like a Generator, but once it sees a cell it will generate that cell infinitely until it sees another. Also updates before other Generators.

cells.name: Trigenerator
cells.description: Generator that generates three cells at once.

cells.name: Bigenerator
cells.description: Generator that generates two cells at once.

cells.name: CW Digenerator
cells.description: Generator that generates two cells at once.

cells.name: CCW Digenerator
cells.description: Generator that generates two cells at once.

cells.name: Tricloner
cells.description: Trigenerator that doesn't rotate the generated cell.

cells.name: Bicloner
cells.description: Bigenerator that doesn't rotate the generated cell.

cells.name: CW Dicloner
cells.description: CW Digenerator that doesn't rotate the generated cell.

cells.name: CCW Dicloner
cells.description: CCW Digenerator that doesn't rotate the generated cell.

cells.name: Transporter
cells.description: Like a Storage cell, but once it holds a cell, it will act like a nudger, then release the cell when it hits a wall. The direction it releases it will be favored towards the rotation of the stored cell, but it will always be perpendicular to the Transporter's direction.

cells.name: Tainter
cells.description: Like a Trash cell, but when it eats a cell it spreads in the direction that the cell came from.

cells.name: Super Replicator
cells.description: Like a Replicator, but it replicates the entire row of cells in front of it.

cells.name: Scissor
cells.description: Upon moving into a cell, it will attempt to split the cell in two and push it out it's sides.

cells.name: Triscissor
cells.description: Scissor with three outputs.

cells.name: Multiplier
cells.description: Scissor that doesn't rotate split cells.

cells.name: Trimultiplier
cells.description: Triscissor that doesn't rotate split cells.

cells.name: CW Scissor
cells.description: Scissor with a straight and curved output.

cells.name: CCW Scissor
cells.description: Scissor with a straight and curved output.

cells.name: CW Multiplier
cells.description: CW Scissor that doesn't rotate split cells.

cells.name: CCW Multiplier
cells.description: CCW Scissor that doesn't rotate split cells.

cells.name: Spooner
cells.description: Like a reversed Forker; if multiple cells go in, only one cell comes out.

cells.name: Trispooner
cells.description: Spooner with three inputs.

cells.name: CW Spooner
cells.description: Spooner with a straight and curved input.

cells.name: CCW Spooner
cells.description: Spooner with a straight and curved input.

cells.name: Compounder
cells.description: Spooner that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: Tricompounder
cells.description: Trispooner that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CW Compounder
cells.description: CW Spooner that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: CCW Compounder
cells.description: CCW Spooner that doesn't rotate cells.

cells.name: IMPLY Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(!A or B) is true. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: CON-IMPLY Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A or !B) is true. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: NIMPLY Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(!A or B) is false. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: CON-NIMPLY Gate
cells.description:
Conditional generator; generates when the condition
(A or !B) is false. Inputs are on it's sides.

cells.name: Converter
cells.description: When a cell enters for the first time, the Converter stores the cell. The next time a cell enters, it will be converted into the stored cell.

cells.name: True Mover
cells.description: Unbreakable Mover that cannot be stopped.

cells.name: True Puller
cells.description: Unbreakable Puller that cannot be stopped.

cells.name: True Driller
cells.description: Unbreakable Driller that cannot be stopped.

cells.name: True Mirror
cells.description: Unbreakable Mirror that cannot be stopped.

cells.name: CW True Gear
cells.description: Unbreakable CW Gear that cannot be stopped.

cells.name: CCW True Gear
cells.description: Unbreakable CCW Gear that cannot be stopped.

cells.name: Phantom
cells.description: Trash that cannot be generated. Additionally, it makes no noise.

cells.name: Lluea
cells.description: A mover with AI. Turns when it hits a wall, can die and turn into it's non-living equivalent from overpopulation. They will also eat infectious cells, and reproduce or gain a force when doing so. If one goes 200 ticks without eating (100 if recently split), it will die.

cells.name: Bar
cells.description: When pushed or pulled, it will attempt to grab the cells at it's sides.

cells.name: Diode Diverger
cells.description: One-way Straight Diverger.

cells.name: Crossdiode Diverger
cells.description: One-way Cross Divergers.

cells.name: Twist Diverger
cells.description: Like a Straight Diverger, but it flips the cell that goes through it like a Twist Generator.

cells.name: Glunki
cells.description: Creates trails to bring cells to itself and digest them, which takes 25 ticks each cell. If a Glunki is enveloped by the Protection effect or goes 250 ticks with no food, it dies and releases the cell. Glunki trails cannot go too far or control is lost.

cells.name: Glunki Trail
cells.description: Glunki trail.

cells.name: Tough Mover
cells.description: Mover but unbreakable from the sides.

cells.name: Spirit Pushable
cells.description: Pushable that cannot be generated.

cells.name: Spirit Slider
cells.description: Slider that cannot be generated.

cells.name: Spirit One-Directional
cells.description: One-Directional that cannot be generated.

cells.name: Spirit Two-Directional
cells.description: Two-Directional that cannot be generated.

cells.name: Spirit Three-Directional
cells.description: Three-Directional that cannot be generated.

cells.name: Super Acid
cells.description: Acid with infinite HP.

cells.name: Acid
cells.description: Acts like an Enemy, but it can only destroy a cell when it gets pushed into one. Acids cannot destroy eachother.

cells.name: Portal
cells.description: Portal. Has an ID and a Target ID. Anything that goes in a portal will come out a portal with the same ID as the entrance portal's Target ID.

cells.name: Time Repulsor
cells.description: Repulses cells some ticks after they get near it. Cannot stack multiple times in the same direction.

cells.name: Coin
cells.description: Adds 1 to a cell's coin count.

cells.name: Coin Diverger
cells.description: Acts like a Cross Diverger to cells with enough coins, acts like a Wall otherwise. Also subtracts that amount of coins from the cell when they pass through.

cells.name: Tough Trash
cells.description: Acts like a Trash on two sides and a Wall on the others.

cells.name: Semitrash
cells.description: Acts like a Trash on two sides and a Pushable on the others.

cells.name: Conveyor Grapulsor
cells.description: Grapulsor but... well, the arrows explain it.

cells.name: Cross Conveyor Grapulsor
cells.description: Two conveyor grapulsors in one.

cells.name: Constructor
cells.description: An unbreakable Builder.

cells.name: Coin Extractor
cells.description: Extracts coins from cells.

cells.name: Silicon
cells.description:
Sticks to other silicon cells.
(Note that stickiness doesn't work perfectly with pulling and grabbing...)

cells.name: Gravitizer
cells.description: Causes cells near it to start falling in the direction it's pointing in.

cells.name: Filter Diverger
cells.description: Like a Straight Diverger, but insert a cell on the top or bottom, and it will delete any cell with the same ID.

cells.name: Realistic Fire
cells.description: Spreads randomly onto nearby cells, floats around randomly, and dies after a random amount of time. Just fun to watch.

cells.name: Creator
cells.description: Like an unbreakable Tetramaker.

cells.name: Particle
cells.description: Basic particle. Stores momentum, but has no other traits.

cells.name: Transformer
cells.description: Transforms the cell in front of it into the cell behind it.

cells.name: Cross Transformer
cells.description: Two Transformers combined.

cells.name: Player
cells.description:
When unpaused, controlled with the arrow keys or WASD.
Additionally, is Player-tagged, meaning if there was at least one player at the start, and then all are destroyed, the level is failed, unless all Enemies are defeated at the same time.

cells.name: Fire
cells.description: Spreads onto adjacent cells and dies after a tick.

cells.name: Megafire
cells.description: Like fire, but affects diagonal neighbors too.

cells.name: Fireball
cells.description: Moving Fire.

cells.name: Megafireball
cells.description: Moving Megafire.

cells.name: Super Enemy
cells.description: Enemy with infinite health; effectively a trash cell that can't delete protected cells.

cells.name: CW Megarotator
cells.description: CW Rotator that affects diagonal neighbors too.

cells.name: CCW Megarotator
cells.description: CCW Rotator that affects diagonal neighbors too.

cells.name: 180 Megarotator
cells.description: 180 Rotator that affects diagonal neighbors too.

cells.name: Super Impulsor
cells.description: Pulls cells towards it from infinite distance with infinite force.

cells.name: Semisilicon
cells.description: Only acts like a silicon on 2 sides.

cells.name: Biintaker
cells.description: Two combined opposite-sided Intakers.

cells.name: Tetraintaker
cells.description: Intaker in all four directions.

cells.name: Slime
cells.description:
Causes nearby cells to stick to each other like Silicon.
Note: Stuck forcers or movers might have trouble propertly exerting force.

cells.name: Scissor Clamper
cells.description: Prevents cells from being scissored.

cells.name: CW Shifter
cells.description: Clockwise-bent Shifter.

cells.name: CCW Shifter
cells.description: Counter-clockwise-bent Shifter.

cells.name: Bishifter
cells.description: Shifter that outputs two cells at once.

cells.name: Trishifter
cells.description: Shifter that outputs three cells at once.

cells.name: CCW Dishifter
cells.description: Shifter that outputs two cells at once.

cells.name: CW Dishifter
cells.description: Shifter that outputs two cells at once.

cells.name: CW Relocator
cells.description: CCW Shifter that does not rotate the outputted cell.

cells.name: CCW Relocator
cells.description: CW Shifter that does not rotate the outputted cell.

cells.name: Birelocator
cells.description: Bishifter that doesn't rotate the outputted cell.

cells.name: Trirelocator
cells.description: Trishifter that doesn't rotate the outputted cell.

cells.name: CCW Direlocator
cells.description: CW Dishifter that doesn't rotate the outputted cell.

cells.name: CW Direlocator
cells.description: CCW Dishifter that doesn't rotate the outputted cell.

cells.name: Degravitizer
cells.description: Un-gravitizes cells.

cells.name: Transmutator
cells.description: Like a Transformer combined with a Shifter.

cells.name: Cross Transmutator
cells.description: Two Transmutators combined.

cells.name: Crasher
cells.description:
Mover + Slicer.
Attempts to push before slicing.

cells.name: Tugger
cells.description: Puller + Slicer.

cells.name: Yanker
cells.description: Puller + Mover + Slicer.

cells.name: Lifter
cells.description: Grabber + Slicer.

cells.name: Hauler
cells.description: Grabber + Mover + Slicer.

cells.name: Dragger
cells.description: Puller + Grabber + Slicer.

cells.name: Mincer
cells.description: Puller + Grabber + Mover + Slicer.

cells.name: Cutter
cells.description:
Driller + Slicer.
Attempts to slice before drilling.

cells.name: Screwdriver
cells.description:
Driller + Mover + Slicer.
Attempts to push, then slice, then drill.

cells.name: Piecer
cells.description: Driller + Puller + Slicer.

cells.name: Slasher
cells.description: Driller + Puller + Mover + Slicer.

cells.name: Script
cells.description:
Executes raw Lua code, with access to the game's variables, as soon as it eats a cell.
Errors will not crash the game, but will be reported in the debugger.
The text input box is quite crap, so you should copy-paste your script instead of typing it here to make your life easier.
Be mindful when running other people's scripts! You don't want anything bad to happen.
